covered: Valid Payload: Tests TC01-03 cover creation with minimal and full payloads, returning 201 with Account JSON and Location header.
Invalid Payload: Tests TC05, TC06, TC12 cover malformed JSON, missing required fields, and empty payload leading to 400.
Duplicate Submission: TC13 tests duplicate handling (201 or 409 depending on policy).
Large Payloads: TC11 validates handling of maximum field sizes.
Validation: Tests TC04 (missing required header), TC08 (header type validation), and TC15 (injection) cover input/header validation.
Server Error Handling: TC10 (503) and TC14 (504) test service unavailability and timeout scenarios.
Field Handling: TC07 confirms extra fields are ignored; TC16 covers partial input; TC17 handles additional headers.
Performance/Concurrency: TC18 tests concurrent account creations.
Regression: TC19 ensures previously fixed issues (e.g., no truncation).
Integration: TC20 verifies retrieved account matches the created one via GET.
gaps: 500 Internal Server Error scenario is not directly tested (only 503/504 covered).
403 Forbidden scenarios (beyond 401 Unauthorized) are not tested.
Rate limiting/throttling tests are not present.
Caching behavior tests (ETag, Cache-Control) are not present.
Tests for URL/method misuse or invalid endpoints beyond the standard path are not present.
recommendations: Add a dedicated 500 Internal Server Error test to simulate DB/application failure during account creation.
Add 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient-permission scenarios beyond 401.
Add tests covering caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control) for POST responses.
Consider explicit tests for additional edge cases (e.g., very long strings, non-ASCII input) to validate sanitization.
